<Link id="l00825" /><CodeLine lineNumber="825"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00826" /><CodeLine lineNumber="826"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This function is the entry point of the DIE selection algorithm. It is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00827" /><CodeLine lineNumber="827"><Highlight kind="comment">/// expected to walk the DIE tree in file order and (though the mediation of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00828" /><CodeLine lineNumber="828"><Highlight kind="comment">/// its helper) call hasValidRelocation() on each DIE that might be a &#39;root</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00829" /><CodeLine lineNumber="829"><Highlight kind="comment">/// DIE&#39; (See DwarfLinker class comment).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00830" /><CodeLine lineNumber="830"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00831" /><CodeLine lineNumber="831"><Highlight kind="comment">/// While walking the dependencies of root DIEs, this function is also called,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00832" /><CodeLine lineNumber="832"><Highlight kind="comment">/// but during these dependency walks the file order is not respected. The</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00833" /><CodeLine lineNumber="833"><Highlight kind="comment">/// TF&#95;DependencyWalk flag tells us which kind of traversal we are currently</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00834" /><CodeLine lineNumber="834"><Highlight kind="comment">/// doing.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00835" /><CodeLine lineNumber="835"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00836" /><CodeLine lineNumber="836"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The recursive algorithm is implemented iteratively as a work list because</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00837" /><CodeLine lineNumber="837"><Highlight kind="comment">/// very deep recursion could exhaust the stack for large projects. The work</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00838" /><CodeLine lineNumber="838"><Highlight kind="comment">/// list acts as a scheduler for different types of work that need to be</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00839" /><CodeLine lineNumber="839"><Highlight kind="comment">/// performed.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00840" /><CodeLine lineNumber="840"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00841" /><CodeLine lineNumber="841"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The recursive nature of the algorithm is simulated by running the &quot;main&quot;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00842" /><CodeLine lineNumber="842"><Highlight kind="comment">/// algorithm (LookForDIEsToKeep) followed by either looking at more DIEs</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00843" /><CodeLine lineNumber="843"><Highlight kind="comment">/// (LookForChildDIEsToKeep, LookForRefDIEsToKeep, LookForParentDIEsToKeep) or</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00844" /><CodeLine lineNumber="844"><Highlight kind="comment">/// fixing up a computed property (UpdateChildIncompleteness,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00845" /><CodeLine lineNumber="845"><Highlight kind="comment">/// UpdateRefIncompleteness).</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00846" /><CodeLine lineNumber="846"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00847" /><CodeLine lineNumber="847"><Highlight kind="comment">/// The return value indicates whether the DIE is incomplete.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00848" /><CodeLine lineNumber="848"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">void</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> DWARFLinker::lookForDIEsToKeep(AddressesMap &amp;AddressesMap,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00849" /><CodeLine lineNumber="849"><Highlight kind="normal">                                    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/dwarf-linker/classic/#a15dd9ce2c2728a22611f39c0fdfce567">UnitListTy</a> &amp;Units,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00850" /><CodeLine lineNumber="850"><Highlight kind="normal">                                    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> DWARFDie &amp;Die, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">const</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> DWARFFile &amp;File,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00851" /><CodeLine lineNumber="851"><Highlight kind="normal">                                    CompileUnit &amp;Cu, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> Flags) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00854" /><CodeLine lineNumber="854"><Highlight kind="normal">  Worklist.emplace&#95;back(Die, Cu, Flags);</Highlight></CodeLine>
